title: Setting up a nest thermostat is almost impossible
text: When going through the flow to setup a google nest thermostat, it fails to connect to the thermostat 95% of the time. I’ve tried both by QR code (the setup flow is completely exited and nothing gets added) and by code and it still won’t connect. This has happened to me every time I have attempted to connect a nest to google home, 5 different time at this point. The last 4 times it did eventually work. Is this app QAed? Do you have integration tests? It appears not.

title: Awesome yet frustrating
text:
One of my favorite apps with one very annoying feature.  The feed automatically refreshes every time you open the app.  
Let’s say you’re working your way down the feed like we all do.  If you switch apps or have to put your phone down, you’re greeted to a completely different feed when you return.    

Sometimes it refreshes as your looking at the feed.  You’ll see something you want to read and as you go to click on it… poof it’s gone.

title: App could get better unlike on Windows
text:
It’s good to be able to keep emails organized and to see what they can be done with. But here are some things that I would find useful to be done in the app. It’s that there’s constant spam mail entering my spam bin, and although I have tried to mute or even permanently delete them without opening the spam mail. The same thing just keeps coming. I have tried doing changes from the website, but there doesn’t seem to be a solution to solve this issue.

Although I can’t do anything, I would suggest Gmail to come up with a solution by coming up with an automated system that will automatically delete all spam messages that are being sent to the user both now and in the future.

Generally though, the automated version of organizing emails has been very useful and convenient, and I thank the developers for this activity.

title: Don’t like the new update.
text:
Hey Google, I’m writing this review because I’ve been having problems with the new update. The search bar is at the bottom of the screen which takes up around 50% of the screen. It’s very irritating whenever I try to swipe out, because it always thinks I’m searching something up. The app freezes and crashes much easier than before, I have no idea if it’s just my phone, or if it’s the app. Many of the useful accessibilities had also gotten removed, 
(like the small arrows at the left bottom corner of the screen) and whenever I try to go back a single tab, it brings me straight back to the search screen. Very unsatisfied by the new format.

title: Waste of time - it does NOT do the job it is supposed to do.
text: I have ADT + that uses Google Home. I receive alerts that I cannot view immediately - Camera is unavailable now. Try back later. I try to view my doorbell camera camera video in realtime - I constantly receive a message that it is unavailable and to try again later. I have uninstalled, reinstalled both apps. It works for 5 minutes and then the error messages return. I have turned off my VPN to see if that works - it does not fix tge issue. ADT + is a waste of time and money because of the Google Homes inadequate and useless service. My mom had a saying - this is too much sugar for a dime. Both services are not worth the aggravation, time spent on trying to fix the issues, and the money I am paying ADT+  for inadequate service.
